<tr><td> The dividing factor (i e., 600 or 300) is used as a constant factor.</td></tr>
<tr><td> This formula is known as Schaeffle’s Formula of body weight estimation.</td></tr>
<tr><td> Since the animal does not stand directly on the weighing scale (or</td></tr>
